son's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":65,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":74,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":109,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Fulletby was born in 1150, in England as the daughter of Ralph de Fulletby and Mrs. Ralph Fulletby. She had at least 1 daughter with Waldron de Wellom."},"et":{"1150–":"1150–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1170–1200":"1170–1200","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Knaresborough Castle, Yorkshire, England":"Knaresborough, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1150–":"1150–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1170–1200":"1170–1200","1120–Male":"1120–Kuol